00:43:31.140 --> 00:43:37.340
I did a study of 17 different
Troparia assigned to tone four

00:43:37.340 --> 00:43:39.910
and came up with a larger
segment of model melodies,

00:43:39.910 --> 00:43:42.660
which I won't bore you
with, but essentially

00:43:42.660 --> 00:43:45.090
when you have these 17
different texts here,

00:43:45.090 --> 00:43:48.380
you can align the model
melodies in different orders

00:43:48.380 --> 00:43:49.860
so you can pick and choose.

00:43:49.860 --> 00:43:52.970
You can start with model melody
one, go to two, go to three,

00:43:52.970 --> 00:43:56.150
or you can start with one and
jump to three, go to four,

00:43:56.150 --> 00:43:57.750
and come back to two, etc.

00:43:57.750 --> 00:44:01.500
So this is the way the Eight Mode
system works as it's been inherited

00:44:01.500 --> 00:44:03.460
through oral transmission
in Georgia.

00:44:03.460 --> 00:44:07.990
And this is of interest for
liturgical scholars and folks

00:44:07.990 --> 00:44:11.730
that study chant transmission,
the Eight Mode system,

00:44:11.730 --> 00:44:18.260 position:56%
so it manifested itself in different
ways in the various centers

00:44:18.260 --> 00:44:23.600
of Christianity, whether in Milan,
Rome, Spain, St. Gall, Jerusalem,

00:44:23.600 --> 00:44:30.990
the various Eastern churches such
