01:14:51.270 --> 01:14:56.150
Yes, so the costume that they're
wearing is called a chokha.

01:14:56.150 --> 01:14:58.140 position:56%
It's not unique to Georgian culture.

01:14:58.140 --> 01:15:04.400
It's a trans-Caucasian, all of the
various groups in the Caucuses,

01:15:04.400 --> 01:15:07.940
all of the various groups in
the Caucuses wear some variant

01:15:07.940 --> 01:15:12.260
of this chokha, which
is a military outfit

01:15:12.260 --> 01:15:16.390
from the 17th and 18th centuries.

01:15:16.390 --> 01:15:19.710
It has many different forms, many
different froms of embroidery,

01:15:19.710 --> 01:15:21.420
etc., in the various regions.

01:15:21.420 --> 01:15:22.990
Some of the common features are

01:15:22.990 --> 01:15:25.870
that it's a tunic worn
outside the clothes with a belt

01:15:25.870 --> 01:15:28.470
on the exterior of the tunic.

01:15:28.470 --> 01:15:31.640
Usually they would have a
short dagger, long sword,

01:15:31.640 --> 01:15:34.730
pistols, rifle, and [laughter]--

01:15:34.730 --> 01:15:37.140
&gt;&gt; Audience Member: None of which
